MAY, 2011

4
01:00:22,465 --> 01:00:23,466
Well…

5
01:00:24,050 --> 01:00:25,719
Hello.

6
01:00:29,264 --> 01:00:31,266
<i>My name is Choi Ung.</i>

7
01:00:31,349 --> 01:00:32,851
CHOI UNG (19, MALE)

8
01:00:32,934 --> 01:00:34,311
Let's look at the first one.

9
01:00:34,394 --> 01:00:36,813
As limit x approaches one,

10
01:00:36,897 --> 01:00:39,524
you can find the limiting value.

11
01:00:39,608 --> 01:00:43,236
So we can think about
the case when it's smaller than one

12
01:00:43,320 --> 01:00:47,824
and when it's bigger than one. Understand?

13
01:00:47,908 --> 01:00:51,244
-Okay. When it's smaller than one…
-Don't look at the camera.

14
01:00:51,328 --> 01:00:54,497
-But it bothers me.
-Just act like it's not here.

15
01:00:54,581 --> 01:00:57,417
How can I? It's right in front of me.

16
01:00:57,500 --> 01:01:00,086
For this case, it goes down like this.

17
01:01:00,170 --> 01:01:02,464
<i>-As you can see…</i>
-So the answer is…

18
01:01:02,547 --> 01:01:04,090
<i>I'm being filmed.</i>

19
01:01:04,174 --> 01:01:05,759
You idiot. Look forward.

20
01:01:05,842 --> 01:01:07,844
Should we look at the next one?

21
01:01:07,928 --> 01:01:11,389
-The limiting value of this is one.
<i>-But it's not just me.</i>

22
01:01:11,473 --> 01:01:13,725
What are you looking at?
Look at the teacher.

23
01:01:13,808 --> 01:01:15,936
The limiting value of this is one as well.

24
01:01:16,019 --> 01:01:19,898
The limiting values of these are the same…

25
01:01:20,482 --> 01:01:22,108
<i>This annoying brat as well.</i>

26
01:01:22,192 --> 01:01:23,318
Let's end it here.

27
01:01:24,778 --> 01:01:26,571
Attention, bow.

28
01:01:27,155 --> 01:01:28,865
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

29
01:01:30,158 --> 01:01:31,618
Where are you going?

30
01:01:31,701 --> 01:01:34,412
It's none of your business.

31
01:01:39,417 --> 01:01:44,464
Sir, can we stop for a moment?
I can't keep working with that idiot.

32
01:01:45,590 --> 01:01:47,842
-"Idiot"?
-We've been filming for days.

33
01:01:47,926 --> 01:01:49,511
Why can't you sit still
when we're filming?

34
01:01:49,594 --> 01:01:52,138
I can't focus at all with you next to me.

35
01:01:52,222 --> 01:01:54,432
How can I
when there is a camera right next to me?

36
01:01:54,516 --> 01:01:57,227
Just focus on the class.
Can't you even do that?

37
01:01:57,310 --> 01:02:00,188
You can ignore me
and focus on class yourself.

38
01:02:00,271 --> 01:02:01,147
Can't you even do that?

39
01:02:01,231 --> 01:02:04,734
I guess you don't care because
your grades couldn't get any worse.

40
01:02:04,818 --> 01:02:07,404
But I won't let you bring down my grades.

41
01:02:09,990 --> 01:02:10,991
You heard her, right?

42
01:02:11,074 --> 01:02:14,452
Whatever. It's your social skills
that couldn't get any worse.

43
01:02:16,329 --> 01:02:17,706
Why did I agree to this?

44
01:02:17,789 --> 01:02:20,542
I know, right? Why did you agree to this?

45
01:02:23,128 --> 01:02:24,587
<i>My name is Kook Yeon-su.</i>

46
01:02:24,671 --> 01:02:25,505
KOOK YEON-SU (19, FEMALE)

47
01:02:26,131 --> 01:02:28,967
<i>I think I first saw Choi Ung
in tenth grade.</i>

48
01:02:31,136 --> 01:02:32,470
This much again?

49
01:02:32,554 --> 01:02:34,764
I'm reading less
because I have exams soon.

50
01:02:34,848 --> 01:02:37,976
You'll read all the books here
by the time you graduate.

51
01:02:38,059 --> 01:02:39,102
Kook Yeon-su…

52
01:02:40,520 --> 01:02:43,106
-Here. Enjoy.
-Thank you.

53
01:02:47,610 --> 01:02:49,446
APRIL'S TOP BOOKWORMS

54
01:02:49,529 --> 01:02:51,072
1ST: CHOI UNG
2ND: KOOK YEON-SU

55
01:02:53,408 --> 01:02:55,118
-Excuse me.
-Yes?

56
01:02:55,201 --> 01:02:56,661
Who is Choi Ung?

57
01:02:56,745 --> 01:02:58,413
He's in first place this month, too?

58
01:02:58,496 --> 01:03:00,206
Oh, Ung?

59
01:03:00,915 --> 01:03:02,584
I think he was over there.

60
01:03:06,838 --> 01:03:07,922
Hey.

61
01:03:09,549 --> 01:03:11,968
<i>I met him somewhere that didn't suit him.</i>

62
01:03:12,052 --> 01:03:13,428
I'm Kook Yeon-su from Class 5.

63
01:03:13,511 --> 01:03:15,221
What's your rank?

64
01:03:15,305 --> 01:03:17,015
-What rank?
-Your grades.

65
01:03:18,641 --> 01:03:19,809
I'm 267th.

66
01:03:21,394 --> 01:03:23,480
The total number of students here…

67
01:03:23,563 --> 01:03:25,565
There are 267 students.

68
01:03:26,900 --> 01:03:29,486
<i>Back then, I just thought
that he was a strange kid.</i>

69
01:03:34,366 --> 01:03:37,243
<i>No, wait. That was the second time we met.</i>

70
01:03:37,994 --> 01:03:40,080
<i>The first time we met
was when we started high school.</i>

71
01:03:40,163 --> 01:03:43,583
The student who entered with
the highest grades is Kook Yeon-su.

72
01:03:46,836 --> 01:03:48,296
Her name's Kook Yeon-su?

73
01:03:48,380 --> 01:03:50,048
What a funny name.

74
01:03:50,131 --> 01:03:54,135
I watched her because she walked
like she was entering a battlefield.

75
01:03:58,348 --> 01:04:00,725
HWIYEONG HIGH SCHOOL ENTRANCE CEREMONY

76
01:04:01,768 --> 01:04:03,603
Hey, look at her skirt.

77
01:04:03,686 --> 01:04:06,314
-She's obviously a teacher's pet.
-She's a stereotype.

78
01:04:06,397 --> 01:04:09,901
-They all have the same style.
-Hey, look at her shoes.

79
01:04:09,984 --> 01:04:11,945
Even my mom wouldn't wear that.

80
01:04:12,028 --> 01:04:14,906
-Spring is finally here.
-How tacky.

81
01:04:14,989 --> 01:04:17,450
The weather is still pretty cold.

82
01:04:17,534 --> 01:04:19,369
<i>We met eyes for the first time,</i>

83
01:04:19,452 --> 01:04:21,412
<i>so I was trying to be nice by smiling.</i>

84
01:04:21,496 --> 01:04:22,580
Hey.

85
01:04:22,664 --> 01:04:24,249
What are you looking at?

86
01:04:26,084 --> 01:04:29,087
<i>But she seemed ill-tempered.</i>

87
01:04:38,221 --> 01:04:42,225
<i>Anyway, I thought I'd never
be involved with him again.</i>

88
01:04:43,226 --> 01:04:44,519
You're here.

89
01:04:44,602 --> 01:04:46,354
Did you think about that offer?

90
01:04:46,437 --> 01:04:48,231
The producer's a friend of mine.

91
01:04:48,314 --> 01:04:49,732
He won't trouble you too much.

92
01:04:49,816 --> 01:04:52,026
You don't have to
if you think it will affect your grades.

93
01:04:52,694 --> 01:04:55,196
-Will it be just me?
-No, with one more student.

94
01:04:55,280 --> 01:04:59,242
It's a documentary where
they observe the best and worst students

95
01:04:59,325 --> 01:05:01,327
for a month as they spend time together.

96
01:05:02,328 --> 01:05:04,372
Anyway, just think about it.

97
01:05:09,669 --> 01:05:13,089
Will I be paid if I agree to do it?

98
01:05:13,173 --> 01:05:14,549
Of course.

99
01:05:20,305 --> 01:05:23,308
<i>He was the exact opposite of me.</i>

100
01:05:24,934 --> 01:05:27,729
Oh, you're here already.

101
01:05:27,812 --> 01:05:28,980
-Hang on.
-All right.

102
01:05:29,063 --> 01:05:31,858
Just a moment.

103
01:05:31,941 --> 01:05:34,986
The ingredients must be here.
Check them thoroughly.

104
01:05:35,069 --> 01:05:37,238
They were in a bad condition last time.

105
01:05:37,322 --> 01:05:39,199
-Check them properly.
-All right.

106
01:05:39,282 --> 01:05:43,745
SEAFOOD SOUP WITH UNG
POTATO SOUP WITH UNG

107
01:05:43,828 --> 01:05:45,371
CHICKEN FEET WITH UNG

108
01:05:45,455 --> 01:05:47,832
-Hello.
-Hello.

109
01:05:47,916 --> 01:05:50,627
He's Ung's father.

110
01:05:50,710 --> 01:05:52,629
-Hello.
-Hello.

111
01:05:53,213 --> 01:05:54,339
Ung!

112
01:05:54,422 --> 01:05:56,341
-Hey. Come over here.
<i>-But things happened</i>

113
01:05:56,424 --> 01:05:58,885
<i>regardless of my intentions.</i>

114
01:05:58,968 --> 01:06:00,970
Why didn't you tell us
about the documentary?

115
01:06:01,054 --> 01:06:03,014
I said I wouldn't do it.

116
01:06:03,097 --> 01:06:06,684
The producer came all the way here.
Why did you say no?

117
01:06:06,768 --> 01:06:09,395
And it's with
the top student in your year.

118
01:06:09,479 --> 01:06:10,730
Of course you should do it!

119
01:06:10,813 --> 01:06:14,901
Of course! We don't know
what he's doing at school.

120
01:06:14,984 --> 01:06:17,445
If you film that,
we'll be able to see what he does.

121
01:06:17,528 --> 01:06:19,614
-That's right.
-Thank you.

122
01:06:19,697 --> 01:06:21,574
-Thank you.
-I said I'm not doing it!

123
01:06:21,658 --> 01:06:23,117
Why would you refuse?

124
01:06:23,201 --> 01:06:26,120
Why would I do that?
I don't want everyone to know my face.

125
01:06:26,204 --> 01:06:28,665
You'll be able
to build a great memory with this.

126
01:06:28,748 --> 01:06:30,583
-Right.
-I'm a senior now, you know.

127
01:06:30,667 --> 01:06:32,961
Don't you think it will affect my grades?

128
01:06:34,796 --> 01:06:36,047
What's he on about?

129
01:06:36,130 --> 01:06:38,925
They are letting you study
with the top student in your grade.

130
01:06:39,008 --> 01:06:40,677
You should be grateful!

131
01:06:40,760 --> 01:06:41,678
I mean…

132
01:06:41,761 --> 01:06:44,555
<i>It was as if it had to happen.</i>

133
01:06:44,639 --> 01:06:46,683
She's kind of weird!

134
01:06:47,308 --> 01:06:50,436
<i>Anyway, that's how it all started.</i>

135
01:06:55,316 --> 01:06:59,153
Choi Ung from Class 1
will be joining us for a month.

136
01:06:59,237 --> 01:07:00,071
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

137
01:07:00,154 --> 01:07:01,447
Be nice to him.

138
01:07:01,531 --> 01:07:05,201
It may be distracting for you
since they'll be filming,

139
01:07:05,285 --> 01:07:07,245
but it will be a fun experience.

140
01:07:07,328 --> 01:07:11,916
And with that,
I hope you all have a great day.

141
01:07:12,000 --> 01:07:12,959
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

142
01:07:37,066 --> 01:07:39,360
<i>It was more bothersome than I thought.</i>

143
01:07:51,372 --> 01:07:53,499
The worst students make the most fuss.

144
01:07:55,209 --> 01:07:57,795
-Are you talking to me?
-Keep your stuff off my desk.

145
01:08:08,389 --> 01:08:12,060
<i>She was way more annoying than I thought.</i>

146
01:08:19,233 --> 01:08:22,111
<i>At first, I tried
to become friends with her.</i>

147
01:08:22,195 --> 01:08:23,321
Hey…

148
01:08:38,210 --> 01:08:39,170
I'm sorry.

149
01:08:52,266 --> 01:08:53,976
Can we…

150
01:09:01,776 --> 01:09:03,194
I said I was sorry.

151
01:09:04,821 --> 01:09:06,489
I'm not sorry.

152
01:09:08,533 --> 01:09:09,701
<i>But what can I do?</i>

153
01:09:10,451 --> 01:09:11,744
<i>We're just so different.</i>

154
01:09:13,579 --> 01:09:14,664
No! Not here!

155
01:09:16,374 --> 01:09:17,542
Darn it.

156
01:09:18,292 --> 01:09:19,377
Go!

157
01:09:21,087 --> 01:09:22,213
Here.

158
01:09:26,259 --> 01:09:27,927
-Hey.
-Over here!

159
01:09:30,680 --> 01:09:31,806
Oh, my.

160
01:09:32,557 --> 01:09:34,183
Darn it. Hey!

161
01:09:34,892 --> 01:09:35,810
Oh, gosh!

162
01:09:44,277 --> 01:09:45,820
Are you okay?

163
01:09:51,784 --> 01:09:53,745
<i>He's so childish.</i>

164
01:09:54,579 --> 01:09:55,580
Ma'am.

165
01:09:56,664 --> 01:10:00,042
How can I solve that
with the L'Hôpital's rule?

166
01:10:01,669 --> 01:10:02,795
Ma'am.

167
01:10:03,337 --> 01:10:07,049
Can we solve this
by using the derived function?

168
01:10:07,133 --> 01:10:08,176
-Ma'am.
-Yes?

169
01:10:08,259 --> 01:10:10,720
-Ma'am.
-All right, kids. Enjoy your lunch.

170
01:10:10,803 --> 01:10:12,054
Ma'am.

171
01:10:13,181 --> 01:10:15,558
<i>She's so selfish.</i>

172
01:10:15,641 --> 01:10:16,642
Ma'am.

173
01:10:17,226 --> 01:10:18,728
<i>THE UNBEARABLE LIGHTNESS OF BEING</i>

174
01:10:20,438 --> 01:10:22,482
I love lying in the shade.

175
01:10:23,858 --> 01:10:25,401
The gentle breeze,

176
01:10:26,861 --> 01:10:28,696
the sunlight shining through the trees…

177
01:10:32,283 --> 01:10:34,118
You're so ridiculous.

178
01:10:36,245 --> 01:10:37,163
Can you move?

179
01:10:37,246 --> 01:10:40,374
Finish reading that
and return it to the library.

180
01:10:48,466 --> 01:10:49,759
This is so nice.

181
01:10:51,010 --> 01:10:53,095
<i>He's so lazy.</i>

182
01:11:13,199 --> 01:11:14,075
Who was that?

183
01:11:15,701 --> 01:11:17,662
Choi Ung! You again?

184
01:11:18,329 --> 01:11:19,705
I told you to be quiet!

185
01:11:21,415 --> 01:11:23,042
<i>Things are already exhausting,</i>

186
01:11:23,125 --> 01:11:25,503
<i>but she just makes it worse.</i>

187
01:11:25,586 --> 01:11:28,631
<i>He's just so pathetic.</i>

188
01:11:32,760 --> 01:11:34,428
Sorry. What was the question?

189
01:11:34,512 --> 01:11:36,472
Pay attention.

190
01:11:38,307 --> 01:11:40,101
Oh, things I hate?

191
01:11:40,184 --> 01:11:41,352
Kook Yeon-su.

192
01:11:45,106 --> 01:11:47,650
I mean, I hate Kook Yeong-su.
She's some girl I know.

193
01:11:47,733 --> 01:11:52,280
I hate pathetic beings.
I hate everyone who's pathetic.

194
01:11:52,363 --> 01:11:54,323
Being selfish. I hate selfish people who--

195
01:11:54,407 --> 01:11:56,158
People who cause trouble for others.

196
01:11:56,242 --> 01:11:59,829
Why can't they just keep to themselves
and not drag others down with them?

197
01:11:59,912 --> 01:12:01,122
Being harsh.

198
01:12:01,205 --> 01:12:02,790
Some people talk without thinking.

199
01:12:02,874 --> 01:12:04,458
They don't think at all.

200
01:12:04,542 --> 01:12:06,085
Look who's talking.

201
01:12:06,168 --> 01:12:09,463
He just doesn't think at all.

202
01:12:09,547 --> 01:12:12,383
Wait. Are you talking about me?

203
01:12:12,466 --> 01:12:14,719
You seemed to be talking about me too.

204
01:12:14,802 --> 01:12:16,971
What? Are you kidding me?

205
01:12:17,054 --> 01:12:18,389
No, I'm totally serious.

206
01:12:19,599 --> 01:12:22,059
Why are you filming this again?

207
01:12:22,143 --> 01:12:25,187
It's a show where the top student helps
the student at the bottom of the class.

208
01:12:25,271 --> 01:12:27,064
-Right?
-I see.

209
01:12:27,148 --> 01:12:28,149
Is this some kind of a test

210
01:12:28,232 --> 01:12:30,484
to see how long you can withstand
someone who has no social skills?

211
01:12:30,568 --> 01:12:33,863
Doing experiments like that
is pretty unethical.

212
01:12:33,946 --> 01:12:37,950
The best student and the worst student.
Which is more anti-social?

213
01:12:38,034 --> 01:12:39,952
When people like her enter society,

214
01:12:40,036 --> 01:12:42,705
they will only tire out
the people around them.

215
01:12:42,788 --> 01:12:45,917
Well, you wouldn't even
be able to participate in society.

216
01:12:46,000 --> 01:12:47,710
How would you know?

217
01:12:50,546 --> 01:12:54,717
What do you think
you'll be like in ten years?

218
01:12:58,596 --> 01:13:01,015
In ten years, I'll be 29.

219
01:13:02,266 --> 01:13:05,519
I'm sure I'd be good at
whatever I'm doing.

220
01:13:06,520 --> 01:13:09,649
I want to live a peaceful life
without doing anything.

221
01:13:09,732 --> 01:13:13,694
I'll be leading people around me,
living an active life.

222
01:13:13,778 --> 01:13:14,737
A successful life.

223
01:13:14,820 --> 01:13:17,698
I hope I'll live a quiet life.

224
01:13:17,782 --> 01:13:19,992
-Anyway…
-One thing I know for sure is that--

225
01:13:20,076 --> 01:13:22,536
…I won't have to see
this annoying face again.

226
01:13:23,496 --> 01:13:25,206
That's what I wanted to say.

